        <name>setState</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="class_fw_fsm_1a281f4c9dd77f0f9e7b08c7609dcbfffe" kindref="member">FwFsm::StateId</ref></type>
          <declname>newStateId</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Function to perform state transition to old state to new state. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>newStateId</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The ID of the desired new state</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
If the state has not changed, indicated by state ID eNoChange the function returns immediately. Otherwise the state instance of the current (old) state will be deleted and with the creator function in array stateTbl an instance of the new state will be allocated and assigned to the current state pointer myState. Also myStateId will be assigned to the ID of the new state. If the new state is not eIdle <ref refid="struct_adxl37x" kindref="compound">Adxl37x</ref> task will be informed that the update process is active. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
